<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920124-0147</DOCNO><DOCID>920124-0147.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief:   Trinova Corp. Posts   $174.5 Million Loss   For Fourth Quarter</HL><DATE>01/24/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   TNV</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MAUMEE, Ohio -- Trinova Corp. reported a fourth-quarterloss of $174.5 million, or $6.18 a share, after taking a$166.4 million charge covering staff reduction costs and thewrite-down of goodwill and some property values.   The maker of industrial, aerospace and automotive partssaid the special charge equaled $5.54 a share and left itwith a net loss for the year of $184.1 million, or $6.52 ashare. In the year-earlier fourth quarter, Trinova had net of$4.5 million, or 16 cents a share, while for all of 1990 itposted a profit of $45.5 million, or $1.51 a share. Salesdeclined 17% to $413.6 million for the quarter and 14% to$1.68 billion for the year.</LP><TEXT>   Trinova had announced on Dec. 18 that it would take a bigfourth-quarter write-off. About $105 million of the chargecame from the write-off of goodwill the company accumulatedfrom 20 companies it had acquired since 1970. Another $61million of the charge related to a writing down the value ofsome properties to a price at which they would sell undercurrent market conditions. Trinova in 1989 set arestructuring provision to cover the sale of some assets.Trinova also announced it will dismiss 800 employees thisyear, primarily in the U.S. and Europe.   Trinova Chairman Darryl F. Allen said that &quot;1991 was atough year for Trinova as the industrial and automotivemarkets we serve were at severely depressed levels and weexperienced the stretch-out or cancellation of aerospace anddefense orders.&quot; He added that Trinova began seeing someimprovement at the end of 1991 in U.S. industrial markets,but that Europe continued to show signs of weakening.   Mr. Allen said that, despite the earnings decline, Trinovagenerated $95 million in cash flow for the year, reducedinventories by $37 million and trimmed its payroll by 9% to17,700 employees.</TEXT></DOC>